---
import Base from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import EmailCTA from './EmailCTA.astro';
import { products } from '../data/products';
interface Props { category:string; slug:string; title:string; description:string; heading:string; eyebrow:string; intro:string; definition:string; selectionTitle:string; selectionText:string; }
const { category,slug,title,description,heading,eyebrow,intro,definition,selectionTitle,selectionText }=Astro.props;
const list=products.filter(product=>product.category===category);
const crumbs=[{name:'Home',url:'/'},{name:'Products',url:'/products/'},{name:heading,url:`/products/${slug}/`}];
const schema={'@context':'https://schema.org','@type':'CollectionPage',name:heading,description,url:`https://ankaili.com/products/${slug}/`};
---
<Base title={title} description={description} breadcrumbs={crumbs} schema={schema}>
  <section class="page-hero"><div class="container"><p class="eyebrow">{eyebrow}</p><h1>{heading}</h1><p>{intro}</p></div></section>
  <section class="section"><div class="container"><div class="answer-block"><strong>Direct answer.</strong> {definition}</div><div class="section-head"><h2>Compare {heading} Models</h2><p class="lead">Review model functions, outputs, installation interfaces and current document requirements before requesting a quotation.</p></div><div class="grid">{list.map(product=><article class="card"><a href={`/products/${product.slug}/`}><img src={product.image} alt={`${product.model} ${category.toLowerCase()}`} width="800" height="800" loading="lazy"></a><p class="eyebrow">{product.model}</p><h3><a href={`/products/${product.slug}/`}>{product.name}</a></h3><p>{product.summary}</p><a class="arrow" href={`/products/${product.slug}/`}>View {product.model} model details</a></article>)}</div></div></section>
  <section class="section tint"><article class="container prose"><h2>{selectionTitle}</h2><p>{selectionText}</p><h3>Define the transformer measurement and control functions</h3><p>Top-oil temperature, traditionally simulated winding temperature and direct winding hot-spot temperature are different values. Define the required local display, cooling stages, alarm or trip contacts, remote output and receiving equipment before comparing suffixes.</p><h3>Provide complete mechanical and electrical interfaces</h3><p>Send the transformer type, existing model, measuring range, contact duty, Pt100 or 4-20 mA requirement, supply, capillary length, bulb, thread, mounting dimensions, quantity and destination country. Replacement projects should include nameplate, terminal and installation photographs.</p><h3>Control the final model specification</h3><p>BWY, BWY2, BWR and BWR2 family names can cover several contact and output configurations. Confirm the complete model code against the current datasheet, outline drawing and terminal diagram before purchase.</p><p>For system integration, review <a href="/applications/substation-remote-temperature-monitoring/">substation remote transformer temperature monitoring</a> and the <a href="/blog/transformer-temperature-controller-wiring/">transformer temperature controller wiring guide</a>.</p></article></section>
  <EmailCTA title={`Request ${heading} Selection`} subject={`${heading} manufacturer and supplier inquiry`} />
</Base>
